**[When AI Becomes Your Financial Adviser: A Global Warning Hidden in Australia’s Gen Z Data](https://asic.gov.au/)**  
AI is rapidly becoming the first point of contact for financial advice. Research from Australia shows nearly one in five Gen Z users already rely on AI tools for financial guidance, with a majority expressing trust in these systems.  

The risk lies not in AI itself, but in misplaced confidence. While AI can simplify concepts and compare products, it lacks fiduciary duty, contextual awareness and regulatory accountability. It can generate convincing but flawed advice, overlook risks and recommend unsuitable strategies.  

Globally, younger consumers are turning to AI before traditional advisers. Trust in AI is rising faster than the safeguards needed to ensure its responsible use. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}  

