**[Cash Isn’t Dead: Digital Payments Surge While Physical Money Still Matters](https://www.bis.org/)**  
Despite rapid growth in digital payments, cash continues to play a significant role in the global financial system. While its use in transactions is declining, it remains important as a store of value, backup mechanism and tool for financial inclusion.  

Digital payments, particularly fast payment systems, are expanding rapidly across both emerging and developed markets. The result is not a complete replacement of cash, but a hybrid system where both digital and physical forms coexist.  

The future of payments will balance innovation with resilience and accessibility. :contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}  

